<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I wanted to use this medium to make a public apology to those people who felt my /ooc in chardok did not represent Noble Blade's honor and reputation well.  <p>I apologize.  <p>I am not apologizing out of necessity to join Noble Blade, but rather because I love and respect Noble Blade and all it's members.  I have come to know a lot of you through raiding so hard and when I offended some of you, I in turn offended all of you.  I also want to assure those who have concerns that about me that if I was tagged by Noble Blade I would represent Noble Blade in the finest light.  If I was to be tagged in future (I have high doubts that this will happen anyway)I want to assure you all that I will live up to and respect the Noble Blade tag in all cases.  I am hoping that those who have come to know me can help relate my good intentions to those who have chosen not to know me and we can all enjoy each others company in the future.  It is very hard to come here and do this because I have a lot of pride which is a flaw I have, but I think you all deserve this apology and I realize I made some mistakes. My only hope is that you remember a time when you have made mistakes as well and you can forgive me for it and give me the chance to prove to you that I can add value to Noble Blade.<p>I love you guys.<p>--------------------</p><p>Vittorrio Dirianiri<br />60 Gravelord of the Rathe<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=155875" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.sighost.com/user/drhell2pay/vittsig.jpg"></a></p>
</FONT>
